        <exercise>
            <statement>
                <p>Consider <m>\fe{g}{t}=\frac{t+9}{t^3}</m>.  Find (and completely simplify) <m>\fe{\sd{g}}{t}</m> and state all numbers where <m>\fe{\sd{g}}{t}</m> is zero or undefined.  Then construct a concavity table for <m>g</m> and state all of the inflection points on <m>g</m>.</p>
